{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-8042696cc98abe2c", "type": "tool_result", "content": "<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (66.5KB). Full output saved to: /inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io/.claude-review/projects/-inspire-qb-ilm-project-video-generation-chenxie-25019-hyr-iHateTheWorld555-github-io/fe91c1aa-1096-44fe-b2c2-7417150f2858/tool-results/btnftocze.txt\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\n=== 2604.18187 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2604.18187\", \"title\": \"Audio-DeepThinker: Progressive Reasoning-Aware Reinforcement Learning for High-Quality Chain-of-Thought Emergence in Audio Language Models\", \"authors\": [\"Xiang He\", \"Chenxing Li\", \"Jinting Wang\", \"Yan Rong\", \"Tianxin Xie\", \"Wenfu Wang\", \"Li Liu\", \"Dong Yu\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\"], \"topic\": \"audio_understanding\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u7406\\u89e3\\u578b\", \"LALM/\\u540e\\u8bad\\u7ec3-GRPO\"], \"contributions\": [\"We propose a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining LLM-based logical evaluation with embedding-based semantic alignment, jointly addressing the dual challenges of reasoning soundness and audio grounding.\", \"We demonstrate that high-quality CoT reasoning can emerge through pure RL exploration from an instruction-tuned LALM without prior chain-of-thought capability, enabled by a progressive two-stage curriculum that establishes foundational patterns and then refines them on challenging boundary cases.\", \"Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR, MMAU-test-mini, and MMSU, winning 1st Place in the Single Model Track of the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge.\", \"Mechanistic interpretability analyses reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, providing novel insights into how audio reasoning capabilities are acquired through exploration.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-Captioner\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate detailed text descriptions of audio inputs in the data construction pipeline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-235B-A22B-Instruct-2507\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate QA pairs from audio descriptions and serves as LLM evaluator for logic asse\n...\n</persisted-output>", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "fe91c1aa-1096-44fe-b2c2-7417150f2858", "uuid": "cb6204f4-fbd1-4829-af60-331492424186", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T10:06:39.316Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "=== 2604.18187 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2604.18187\", \"title\": \"Audio-DeepThinker: Progressive Reasoning-Aware Reinforcement Learning for High-Quality Chain-of-Thought Emergence in Audio Language Models\", \"authors\": [\"Xiang He\", \"Chenxing Li\", \"Jinting Wang\", \"Yan Rong\", \"Tianxin Xie\", \"Wenfu Wang\", \"Li Liu\", \"Dong Yu\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.CL\"], \"topic\": \"audio_understanding\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u7406\\u89e3\\u578b\", \"LALM/\\u540e\\u8bad\\u7ec3-GRPO\"], \"contributions\": [\"We propose a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining LLM-based logical evaluation with embedding-based semantic alignment, jointly addressing the dual challenges of reasoning soundness and audio grounding.\", \"We demonstrate that high-quality CoT reasoning can emerge through pure RL exploration from an instruction-tuned LALM without prior chain-of-thought capability, enabled by a progressive two-stage curriculum that establishes foundational patterns and then refines them on challenging boundary cases.\", \"Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR, MMAU-test-mini, and MMSU, winning 1st Place in the Single Model Track of the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge.\", \"Mechanistic interpretability analyses reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, providing novel insights into how audio reasoning capabilities are acquired through exploration.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-Captioner\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate detailed text descriptions of audio inputs in the data construction pipeline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-235B-A22B-Instruct-2507\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate QA pairs from audio descriptions and serves as LLM evaluator for logic assessment\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"DeepSeek V3.1\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to generate reference reasoning chains in the data construction pipeline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AVQA\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 1 providing 39,412 samples with sound events and QA pairs\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioMCQ\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2 providing reasoning-intensive boundary cases\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioSet\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MagnaTagATune\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Switchboard\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MusicBench\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CoclScene\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MusicAVQA\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"IEMOCAP\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training dataset for stage 2\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"BGE-M3\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to compute embedding semantic similarity between generated and reference reasoning chains\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-30B-A3B-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Base model fine-tuned with RL for the proposed method\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen3-Omni-Thinking\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Alternative base model used to verify generalization of the framework\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAR\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Deep audio reasoning benchmark evaluating accuracy and Rubrics scores\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAU\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Large-scale multi-task audio understanding benchmark with test-mini and full test sets\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMSU\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Multimodal speech understanding benchmark focusing on semantic, phonological, and paralinguistic domains\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o mini Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Closed-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Closed-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini 2.0 Flash\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Closed-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini 2.5 Flash\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Closed-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2-Audio-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Audio Flamingo 2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Audio Flamingo 3\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Kimi-Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen-2.5-Omni\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Covo-Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Step-Audio 2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Open-source baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Audio-Reasoner\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"RL fine-tuned baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"R1-AQA\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"RL fine-tuned baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Omni-R1\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"RL fine-tuned baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Ke-Omni-R\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"RL fine-tuned baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CESAR\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"RL fine-tuned baseline model compared against in experiments\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Audio-Thinker\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"RL fine-tuned baseline model compared against in experiments; also used as an ablation reward baseline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SWIFT\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training framework used for RL optimization\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Megatron-LM\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Training framework used for RL optimization\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Large Audio-Language Models (LALMs) have made significant progress in audio understanding, yet they primarily operate as perception-and-answer systems without explicit reasoning processes. Existing methods for enhancing audio reasoning rely either on supervised chain-of-thought (CoT) fine-tuning, which is limited by training data quality, or on reinforcement learning (RL) with coarse rewards that do not directly evaluate reasoning quality. As a result, the generated reasoning chains often appear well-structured yet lack specific acoustic grounding. We propose Audio-DeepThinker, a framework built on two core ideas. First, we introduce a hybrid reasoning similarity reward that directly supervises the quality of generated reasoning chains by combining an LLM evaluator assessing logical path alignment, key step coverage, and analytical depth with an embedding similarity component enforcing semantic alignment with reference reasoning chains. Second, we propose a progressive two-stage curriculum that enables high-quality CoT reasoning to emerge through pure RL exploration, without any supervised reasoning fine-tuning, from an instruction-tuned model that possesses no prior chain-of-thought capability. Stage 1 trains on foundational audio QA with the hybrid reward to foster basic reasoning patterns, while Stage 2 shifts to acoustically challenging boundary cases with an LLM-only reward for greater reasoning diversity. Audio-DeepThinker achieves state-of-the-art results on MMAR (74.0%), MMAU-test-mini (78.5%), and MMSU (77.26%), winning 1st Place in the Interspeech 2026 Audio Reasoning Challenge (Single Model Track). Interpretability analyses further reveal that RL training primarily reshapes upper-layer MoE gating mechanisms and that reasoning tokens crystallize progressively in the upper transformer layers, offering mechanistic insights into how audio reasoning emerges through exploration.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T06:09:40.741566\"}\n=== 2605.21008 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2605.21008\", \"title\": \"A Survey of Audio Reasoning in Multimodal Foundation Models\", \"authors\": [], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [], \"topic\": \"\", \"tags\": [], \"contributions\": [\"We define common notations and formalize audio reasoning across text-output, speech-output, audio-visual, and agentic settings under a unified framework.\", \"We summarize the foundations of audio reasoning models, including audio encoders, modality projectors, LLM backbones, speech tokenization, alignment, instruction tuning, preference optimization, and parameter-efficient adaptation.\", \"We organize studies into Audio-to-Text, Audio-to-Speech, Audio-Visual, and Agentic Audio Reasoning, covering CoT prompting, supervised fine-tuning, reinforcement learning, latency-aware spoken interaction, cross-modal grounding, and tool-augmented reasoning.\", \"We summarize evaluation protocols, identify their limitations, and outline open challenges for building robust, efficient, and natively grounded audio reasoning systems.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAU\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u901a\\u7528\\u97f3\\u9891\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u3001\\u58f0\\u97f3\\u3001\\u97f3\\u4e50\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAU-Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u901a\\u7528\\u97f3\\u9891\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u3001\\u58f0\\u97f3\\u3001\\u97f3\\u4e50\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAR\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u901a\\u7528\\u97f3\\u9891\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u3001\\u58f0\\u97f3\\u3001\\u97f3\\u4e50\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMSU\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u805a\\u7126\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoxEval\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u805a\\u7126\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CMDAR\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u4e2d\\u6587\\u97f3\\u9891\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u3001\\u58f0\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u4e0e\\u5f00\\u653e\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Spoken-MQA\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u53e3\\u8bed\\u6570\\u5b66\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u4e0e\\u5f00\\u653e\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WildSpeech-Bench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7aef\\u5230\\u7aef\\u4ea4\\u4e92\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5f00\\u653e\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"URO-Bench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7aef\\u5230\\u7aef\\u4ea4\\u4e92\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u4e0e\\u5f00\\u653e\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VoiceAgentBench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u591a\\u8f6e\\u5de5\\u5177\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u4e0e\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SAKURA\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u591a\\u8df3\\u97f3\\u9891\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u3001\\u58f0\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WavBench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7aef\\u5230\\u7aef\\u4ea4\\u4e92\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u4e0e\\u5f00\\u653e\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"\\u03c4-Voice\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7aef\\u5230\\u7aef\\u4ea4\\u4e92\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioRAG\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u97f3\\u9891\\u68c0\\u7d22\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u3001\\u58f0\\u97f3\\u3001\\u97f3\\u4e50\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Full-Duplex-Bench-v3\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u591a\\u8f6e\\u5de5\\u5177\\u4f7f\\u7528\\u4e0e\\u63a8\\u7406\\u9886\\u57df\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\\u6d4b\\u8bd5\\u6570\\u636e\\u96c6\\uff0c\\u4ec5\\u5305\\u542b\\u8bed\\u97f3\\uff0c\\u5c01\\u95ed\\u5f0f\\u8bc4\\u4f30\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Abstract\\nReasoning has become a defining capability of modern foundation models, yet its development in the audio modality remains limited. Audio poses challenges that are distinct from those of text and vision. It is continuous, temporally dense, and contains linguistic, paralinguistic, and environmental information at multiple time scales. As a result, audio reasoning models must align acoustic signals with the discrete semantic space of large language models, while still preserving fine-grained information needed for reliable inference. Progress is also limited by three major obstacles: the scarcity of genuinely audio-grounded reasoning data, shortcut learning and modality hallucination, and the tension between reasoning depth and real-time latency in spoken interaction. In this paper, we present the first dedicated survey of audio reasoning. We provide a unified formulation that distinguishes direct predictive modeling from reasoning-augmented generation, review the architectural and training foundations of audio reasoning models, and systematically organize recent advances in Audio-to-Text, Audio-to-Speech, Audio-Visual Reasoning and Agentic Audio Reasoning. We further examine emerging paradigms such as Chain-of-Thought prompting, supervised fine-tuning, reinforcement learning, and latency-aware spoken interaction, and discuss evaluation practices, open challenges, and future directions. Our goal is to offer a coherent roadmap for developing robust, efficient, and natively grounded audio reasoning systems.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-06-01T04:02:02.436874\"}\n=== 2605.22012 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2605.22012\", \"title\": \"LatentOmni: Rethinking Omni-Modal Understanding via Unified Audio-Visual Latent Reasoning\", \"authors\": [\"Yifan Dai\", \"Zhenhua Wu\", \"Bohan Zeng\", \"Daili Hua\", \"Jialing Liu\", \"Bozhou Li\", \"Yuran Wang\", \"Chengzhuo Tong\", \"Hao Liang\", \"Xiaochen Ma\", \"Junbo Niu\", \"Tianyu Guo\", \"Yang Shi\", \"Yue Ding\", \"Yiyan Ji\", \"Bingyin Mei\", \"Yushuo Guan\", \"Yuanxing Zhang\", \"Pengfei Wan\", \"Fangcheng Fu\", \"Wentao Zhang\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.CL\", \"cs.CV\"], \"topic\": \"\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u7406\\u89e3\\u578b\", \"LALM/\\u6f5c\\u5728\\u8868\\u793a\"], \"contributions\": [\"Proposes LatentOmni, a cross-modal reasoning framework that interleaves textual reasoning with audio-visual latent states in a unified latent space.\", \"Introduces feature-level supervision to align latent reasoning states with task-relevant sensory features and Omni-Sync Position Embedding (OSPE) to maintain temporal consistency between audio and visual modalities.\", \"Constructs LatentOmni-Instruct-35K, a dataset of audio-visual interleaved reasoning trajectories for supervising latent-space reasoning.\", \"Demonstrates state-of-the-art open-source performance on multiple audio-visual reasoning benchmarks, consistently outperforming explicit text CoT baselines.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2.5-Omni-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u57fa\\u5ea7\\u6a21\\u578b\\uff0cLatentOmni\\u5728\\u5176\\u57fa\\u7840\\u4e0a\\u6784\\u5efa\\uff0cOSPE\\u4e5f\\u6269\\u5c55\\u81ea\\u5176\\u65f6\\u95f4\\u5bf9\\u9f50\\u591a\\u6a21\\u6001RoPE\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ASID\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"\\u539f\\u59cb\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891\\u5b57\\u5e5