er_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"WorldSense\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7269\\u7406\\u548c\\u65f6\\u7a7a\\u5e38\\u8bc6\\u5168\\u6a21\\u6001\\u8bc4\\u4f30\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"OmniVideoBench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u8de8\\u6a21\\u6001\\u5bf9\\u9f50\\u548cQA\\u5168\\u6a21\\u6001\\u8bc4\\u4f30\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LVOmniBench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u957f\\u89c6\\u9891\\u591a\\u611f\\u5b98\\u7406\\u89e3\\u5168\\u6a21\\u6001\\u8bc4\\u4f30\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VideoMME\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"\\u7528\\u4e8e\\u7eaf\\u89c6\\u89c9\\u534f\\u8bae\\u4e0b\\u8bc4\\u4f30\\u89c6\\u89c9\\u6f5c\\u5728\\u63a8\\u7406\\u65b9\\u6cd5\\u7684\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VideoLLaMA2-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u5f00\\u6e90\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891MLLM\\u57fa\\u7ebf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MiniCPM-o-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u5f00\\u6e90\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891MLLM\\u57fa\\u7ebf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VITA-1.5-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u5f00\\u6e90\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891MLLM\\u57fa\\u7ebf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"HumanOmniV2-7B\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u5f00\\u6e90\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891MLLM\\u57fa\\u7ebf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Baichuan-Omni-1.5\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u5f00\\u6e90\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891MLLM\\u57fa\\u7ebf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"OmniVinci\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5b9e\\u9a8c\\u4e2d\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u5f00\\u6e90\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891MLLM\\u57fa\\u7ebf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Explicit Text CoT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u6d88\\u878d\\u57fa\\u7ebf\\uff0c\\u79fb\\u9664\\u4ea4\\u9519\\u97f3\\u89c6\\u9891\\u7247\\u6bb5\\u7684\\u7eaf\\u6587\\u672cCoT\\u5fae\\u8c03\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Vanilla SFT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u6d88\\u878d\\u57fa\\u7ebf\\uff0c\\u65e0\\u6f5c\\u5728\\u63a8\\u7406\\u7684\\u6807\\u51c6\\u5fae\\u8c03\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"LVR\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5728VideoMME\\u4e0a\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u89c6\\u89c9\\u6f5c\\u5728\\u63a8\\u7406\\u65b9\\u6cd5\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Monet\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u5728VideoMME\\u4e0a\\u5bf9\\u6bd4\\u7684\\u89c6\\u89c9\\u6f5c\\u5728\\u63a8\\u7406\\u65b9\\u6cd5\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"GPT-4o\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u95ed\\u6e90\\u53c2\\u8003\\u7cfb\\u7edf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-2.0-Flash\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u95ed\\u6e90\\u53c2\\u8003\\u7cfb\\u7edf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-2.5-Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u95ed\\u6e90\\u53c2\\u8003\\u7cfb\\u7edf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini-3-Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"\\u95ed\\u6e90\\u53c2\\u8003\\u7cfb\\u7edf\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Joint audio-visual reasoning is essential for omnimodal understanding, yet current multimodal large language models (MLLMs) still struggle when reasoning requires fine-grained evidence from both modalities. A central limitation is that explicit text-based chain-of-thought (CoT) compresses continuous audio-visual signals into discrete tokens, weakening temporal grounding and shifting intermediate reasoning toward language priors. We argue that a unified latent space is a better medium for such reasoning because it preserves dense sensory information while remaining compatible with autoregressive generation. Based on this insight, we propose \\\\textbf{LatentOmni}, a cross-modal reasoning framework that interleaves textual reasoning with audio-visual latent states. LatentOmni introduces feature-level supervision to align latent reasoning states with task-relevant sensory features and uses Omni-Sync Position Embedding (OSPE) to maintain temporal consistency between latent audio and visual states. We further construct \\\\textbf{LatentOmni-Instruct-35K}, a dataset of audio-visual interleaved reasoning trajectories for supervising latent-space reasoning. Comprehensive evaluation across multiple audio-visual reasoning benchmarks demonstrates that LatentOmni achieves the best performance among the evaluated open-source models and consistently outperforms the Explicit Text CoT baseline, supporting latent-space joint reasoning as a promising path toward stronger omnimodal understanding.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-05-24T06:22:33.229116\"}\n=== 2402.07729 ===\n{\"arxiv_id\": \"2402.07729\", \"title\": \"AIR-Bench: Benchmarking Large Audio-Language Models via Generative Comprehension\", \"authors\": [\"Qian Yang\", \"Jin Xu\", \"Wenrui Liu\", \"Yunfei Chu\", \"Ziyue Jiang\", \"Xiaohuan Zhou\", \"Yichong Leng\", \"Yuanjun Lv\", \"Zhou Zhao\", \"Chang Zhou\", \"Jingren Zhou\"], \"year\": 2024, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"eess.AS\", \"cs.CL\", \"cs.LG\", \"cs.SD\"], \"topic\": \"speech_dataset\", \"tags\": [\"Eval\", \"LALM\", \"Eval/\\u57fa\\u51c6\", \"Eval/LLM\"], \"contributions\": [\"AIR-Bench is the first generative evaluation benchmark for large audio-language models, encompassing a wide array of audio such as speech, natural sounds, and music.\", \"A novel audio mixing strategy with loudness control and temporal dislocation is proposed to enhance the complexity of the audio.\", \"A unified, objective, and reproducible evaluation framework has been developed to assess the quality of generative hypotheses.\", \"A thorough evaluation of 9 models was conducted for the purpose of benchmarking.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2305.11000\", \"title\": \"SpeechGPT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated dedicated LALM model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2305.13600\", \"title\": \"BLSP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated dedicated LALM model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2310.06101\", \"title\": \"SALMONN\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated dedicated LALM model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2311.00419\", \"title\": \"Qwen-Audio-Chat\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated dedicated LALM model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2305.16300\", \"title\": \"PandaGPT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated multimodal model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2306.09093\", \"title\": \"Macaw-LLM\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated multimodal model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2305.15207\", \"title\": \"NExT-GPT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Evaluated multimodal model\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"2212.04356\", \"title\": \"Whisper-large-v2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used as the ASR component in the cascaded baseline\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Recently, instruction-following audio-language models have received broad attention for human-audio interaction. However, the absence of benchmarks capable of evaluating audio-centric interaction capabilities has impeded advancements in this field. Previous models primarily focus on assessing different fundamental tasks, such as Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR), and lack an assessment of the open-ended generative capabilities centered around audio. Thus, it is challenging to track the progression in the Large Audio-Language Models (LALMs) domain and to provide guidance for future improvement. In this paper, we introduce AIR-Bench (\\\\textbf{A}udio \\\\textbf{I}nst\\\\textbf{R}uction \\\\textbf{Bench}mark), the first benchmark designed to evaluate the ability of LALMs to understand various types of audio signals (including human speech, natural sounds, and music), and furthermore, to interact with humans in the textual format. AIR-Bench encompasses two dimensions: \\\\textit{foundation} and \\\\textit{chat} benchmarks. The former consists of 19 tasks with approximately 19k single-choice questions, intending to inspect the basic single-task ability of LALMs. The latter one contains 2k instances of open-ended question-and-answer data, directly assessing the comprehension of the model on complex audio and its capacity to follow instructions. Both benchmarks require the model to generate hypotheses directly. We design a unified framework that leverages advanced language models, such as GPT-4, to evaluate the scores of generated hypotheses given the meta-information of the audio. Experimental results demonstrate a high level of consistency between GPT-4-based evaluation and human evaluation. By revealin", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false, "persistedOutputPath": "/inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io/.claude-review/projects/-inspire-qb-ilm-project-video-generation-chenxie-25019-hyr-iHateTheWorld555-github-io/fe91c1aa-1096-44fe-b2c2-7417150f2858/tool-results/btnftocze.txt", "persistedOutputSize": 68089}}
